<html>
  <problem>
    
      <p>A block of mass M is sliding down an inclined plane and is accelerating.  Which of the following statements are true?</p>

    <optionresponse texlayout="horizontal" max="10" randomize="no" loncapaid="11">
        <ul>
            <li>
              
                <p>The frictional force must be zero</p>
              
          <optioninput location="random" name="Foil1" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
          </optioninput>
          </li>
          <li>
          
                    <p>The frictional force must be less than the component of Mg down the plane</p>
              
          <optioninput location="random" name="Foil2" options="('True','False')" correct="True">
</optioninput>
        </li>
        <li>
          
                <p>The normal force of the plane is equal to the weight of the block</p>
              
                      <optioninput location="random" name="Foil3" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>
        </li>
        <li>
          
<p>The surface may or may not have friction, even though the block is accelerating</p>
              
          <optioninput location="random" name="Foil4" options="('True','False')" correct="True">
</optioninput>
        </li>
        <li>
          
                <p>If the block's mass were doubled, its acceleration would be doubled</p>
              
                        <optioninput location="random" name="Foil5" options="('True','False')" correct="False">
</optioninput>

      </li>
      </ul>
    </optionresponse>
  </problem>
</html>
